Time Series Analysis and Models

amazon.stock = df %>% filter(Stock == "Amazon") %>% arrange(Date)

ggtsdisplay(amazon.stock %>% select(Close), main = "Close Price")

ts.model = auto.arima(amazon.stock %>% select(Close), seasonal = TRUE)
ggtsdisplay(ts.model$residuals, main = "Arima(5, 2, 0)")

ts.model %>% summary()
## Series: amazon.stock %>% select(Close) 
## ARIMA(5,2,0) 
## 
## Coefficients:
##           ar1      ar2      ar3      ar4      ar5
##       -0.8474  -0.6987  -0.5458  -0.3928  -0.1820
## s.e.   0.0136   0.0172   0.0183   0.0173   0.0137
## 
## sigma^2 estimated as 46.94:  log likelihood=-17604.23
## AIC=35220.47   AICc=35220.48   BIC=35259.88
## 
## Training set error measures:
##                       ME     RMSE      MAE         MPE     MAPE     MASE
## Training set 0.009030618 6.846678 3.303552 0.005902809 2.655405 1.107842
##                     ACF1
## Training set -0.02547026
amazon.stock = amazon.stock %>% mutate(ts.residuals = ts.model$residuals)

res.lm.model = lm(data = amazon.stock, formula = ts.residuals ~ Open + Volume)
res.lm.model %>% summary()
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = ts.residuals ~ Open + Volume, data = amazon.stock)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -75.480  -1.469  -0.009   1.211 132.448 
## 
## Coefficients:
##               Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)  
## (Intercept) -2.444e-01  1.662e-01  -1.470   0.1415  
## Open         6.604e-05  3.367e-04   0.196   0.8445  
## Volume       3.066e-08  1.292e-08   2.373   0.0177 *
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 6.845 on 5265 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.001107,   Adjusted R-squared:  0.0007272 
## F-statistic: 2.916 on 2 and 5265 DF,  p-value: 0.05421
amazon.stock = amazon.stock %>% 
  mutate(predictions = ts.model$fitted + res.lm.model$fitted.values)
amazon.stock$residuals = c(amazon.stock$Close - amazon.stock$predictions)

ggplot(data = amazon.stock, aes(x = Date)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = Close, color = "red")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = predictions, color = "blue")) +
  xlab("time") +
  ylab("Close Price of Amazon Stock") +
  ggtitle("ARIMA(5, 2, 0)")
